29 Aug 2019 15:23






Oh, this rules.

+rambles

-stop


Something I've always liked on the site are skips where religion and science meet - more specifically where religion is treated as a science, and this really scratches that itch. The existence of human souls are accepted as a matter of course - quantifiable into terabytes - and a human being is literally preserved as bread and wine by imitating Christ.

The way the two interact here is just spectacular, and I especially love the little touches in the containment procedures like the Site Director being designated as an abbot and the specification that technicians 'are to consist of Foundation personnel who are Capuchin monks.' There's a lot of nice world-building there, and you get the sense that this kind of anomaly is something the Foundation is used to accommodating (along with the mention of them working with the Vatican).

I'm not too sure about the object class, though. I get that it evokes the same sort of atmosphere as the 001 that shares it, but I don't feel like it adds that much to the narrative here in a way that one of the standard object classes wouldn't. Still, that's a minor concern, and apart from that it's a wholehearted upvote from me!




+1







